</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[806,1421,555,883]" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">
<emphasis box="[806,1182,555,577]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">
Larva and puparium (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1169,555,576]" captionStart="Figures 25–27" captionStartId="42.[144,234,1609,1630]" captionTargetBox="[146,1852,426,1576]" captionTargetId="figure-0@42.[144,1856,421,1580]" captionTargetPageId="42" captionText="Figures 25–27. Third stage larval Copestylum, whole larva, head to the right; scale bar = 7 mm. 25. Copestylum apiciferum; 26, Copestylum isabellina; 27, Copestylum sica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443496" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443496/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">Fig. 25</figureCitation>
):
</emphasis>
Anterior fold with band of spicules rounded not tapered at outer limits. Longest vestiture of dorsum of prothorax shorter than longest spicules on the anterior fold. Posterior breathing tube about as long as wide above poorly defined TR (
<figureCitation box="[856,937,708,730]" captionStart="Figures 66–67" captionStartId="50.[144,234,1640,1659]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,1197,1607]" captionTargetId="figure-50@50.[303,1263,1197,1609]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Figures 66–67. Puparium of Copestylum apiciferum, scanning electron photomicrographs, scales as indicated on images. 66, posterior breathing tube (prp), dorsal view width at TR = 1.25 mm; 67, pupal spiracle, dorsolateral view length = 0.85 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443516/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
). AP tapering to half width of TR and 0.9¥ as long as TR is wide. Pupal spiracles separated by 2.1¥ their length and openings not clustered closely together at the apex but spread down the upper third and separated by about 2¥ diameter of an opening (
<figureCitation box="[814,895,861,883]" captionStart="Figures 66–67" captionStartId="50.[144,234,1640,1659]" captionTargetBox="[303,1263,1197,1607]" captionTargetId="figure-50@50.[303,1263,1197,1609]" captionTargetPageId="50" captionText="Figures 66–67. Puparium of Copestylum apiciferum, scanning electron photomicrographs, scales as indicated on images. 66, posterior breathing tube (prp), dorsal view width at TR = 1.25 mm; 67, pupal spiracle, dorsolateral view length = 0.85 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5443516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5443516/files/figure.png" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">Fig. 67</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="18" pageNumber="715" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="18.[806,1421,927,1255]" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">
<emphasis box="[806,1273,927,948]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">
Taxonomic notes: 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1010,1273,927,948]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiciferum">Copestylum apiciferum</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
is separated from 
<taxonomicName authority="(Williston, 1891)" baseAuthorityName="Williston" baseAuthorityYear="1891" box="[868,1226,957,979]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadratum">
<emphasis box="[868,1029,957,979]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">C. quadratum</emphasis>
(Williston, 1891)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier, 2009" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[1285,1380,957,979]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="milae" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1285,1380,957,979]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">C. milae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel pageId="18" pageNumber="715" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the pattern of distribution formed by spicules at the ends of the band on the anterior fold that are rounded not tapered, AP not as long as TR is wide and the distribution of the openings on the pupal spiracles, which are distributed over the apical third and not clustered at the apex. 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Townsend" baseAuthorityYear="1895" box="[1125,1391,1141,1162]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="apiciferum">
<emphasis box="[1125,1391,1141,1162]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">Copestylum apiciferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated from 
<taxonomicName authority="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier, 2009" authorityName="Rotheray &amp; Marcos-García &amp; Hancock &amp; Pérez-Bañón &amp; Maier" authorityYear="2009" box="[990,1146,1171,1193]" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Copestylum" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hidalgense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[990,1146,1171,1193]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="715">C. hidalgense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1154,1241,1172,1193]" pageId="18" pageNumber="715" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
by the absence of spicules on the anterodorsal margin of the mesothorax.
</paragraph>
